SCRUB TYPHUS - INDIA: (MIZORAM) SUSPECTED
*****************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 5 Jan 2018 14:50 IST
Source: India Today, Press Trust of India (PTI) report [edited]
http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/scrub-typhus-virus-one-persons-dies-47-infected-in-mizoram/1/1124158.html


One person died and at least 47 people have been infected with suspected scrub typhus virus at Phullen village in Aizawl district [Mizoram], health department officials said today [5 Jan 2018]. Nodal officer of the State Integrated Disease Surveillance Programme (IDSP) Dr Pachuau Lalmalsawma, who visited Phullen village yesterday [4 Jan 2018] said the spread of the disease has been contained and the patients were given medical treatment.

Phullen village is about 125 km [about 78 mi] north east of the state capital [Aizawl]. Lalmalsawma said that the 1st case was detected during the last part of November [2017] and new infection detected till [3 Jan 2018].

Scrub typhus is a miteborne disease caused by _Orientia tsutsugamushi_ (formerly _Rickettsia tsutsugamushi_). Symptoms are fever, a primary lesion, a macular rash, and lymphadenopathy. Cases of scrub typhus infection have been detected in Champhai, Aizawl, and Lunglei districts.

Over 100 people have died in the state during the past few years due to scrub typhus infection, health department officials said.

