[ProMED-mail has posted multiple reports of scrub typhus in several Indian states in the past, especially since 2011. For background information, see ProMED-mail post Scrub typhus - India (05): background 20111208.3546.

Maps of India: http://www.mapsofindia.com/maps/india/india-political-map.htm and https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5541468,63548.
Phullen is a town in Aizawl district, in the Indian state of Mizoram. A map showing the location of Phullen can be found at https://goo.gl/maps/1XgbN7QpVav. Aizawl district is one of the 8 districts of Mizoram state; the city of Aizawl, with a population of 293 416 residents in 2011, is the district headquarters and the capital of the state of Mizoram (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aizawl). A map of Mizoram districts can be found at https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Aizawl_district#/media/File:India_Mizoram_Aizawl_map_EN.svg. Aizawl district is bounded on the northeast by the state of Manipur, where ProMED-mail recently posted a report of scrub typhus (Scrub typhus - India (03): (MN) fatal 20170728.5211944). - Mod.ML]
